<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Tongaat-Hulett headline EPS jumps 35 pct.</title>
<headline>Tongaat-Hulett headline EPS jumps 35 pct.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended March 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>Shr, (cts)</p>
<p>    - headline		472.3	 vs  350.4</p>
<p>    - net		     574.6	 vs  427.3</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 175.0	 vs  130.0</p>
<p>NOTE - Analysts polled by Reuters forecast the Tongaat group's headline earnings per share rising to between 460 cents and 482.1 cents with consensus at 469.1. The dividend was seen in a range of 164.0 to 175.5 cents with consensus at 170.2.  </p>
<p>    Net earnings	    547.43	vs  397.45</p>
<p>    Headline earnings     450.01	vs  325.90</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   735.81	vs  481.96</p>
<p>Tax</p>
<p>     - operations	   189.51	vs  129.01</p>
<p>- non-trading/exceps 2.63 rebate vs  44.47 rebate</p>
<p>    Interest received     97.61	 vs  20.13</p>
<p>    Turnover		  4,697.48    vs  4,124.68</p>
<p>Full name: The Tongaat-Hulett Group Ltd</p>
<p>Div payable July 16</p>
<p>on register June 13</p>
<p>Note - The group said it had decided to award capitalisation shares determined by the ratio that 132 cents bears to the weighted average trading price of the company's shares on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange during the three day period ending July 3 for every share held.</p>
<p>Shareholders may elect to receive a cash dividend instead.</p>
<p>Tongaat-Hulett said it wold apply to have the new shares listed in Johannesburg and London.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482-1003</p>
</text>
